The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Rail fine on Laloo party

 Patna, Jan. 6 (PTI): Acting on the directive of the Election Commission, railway authorities have imposed a penalty of Rs 28,000 on the Rashtriya Janata Dal (RJD) for defacing public property on rail premises at Patna and Hajipur by putting up posters, banners and hoardings.

 The notice sent to Bihar RJD president Abdul Bari Siddiqui has asked him to deposit the penalty at the East Central Railway (ECR)?s zonal office by January 13, ECR chief public relations officer A.K. Chandra said here today.

 While a fine of Rs 15,000 has been earmarked as charges for removing posters, banners and hoardings put up for the December 23 rally ? which was eventually called off ? and cleaning the walls of Patna railway station, Rs 13,000 has been earmarked for Hajipur station, he added.

 Similar notices have also been sent to the Lok Janshakti Party and Bharatiya Janata Party state headquarters asking, the two parties to pay a penalty of Rs 2,000 each for the defacement of railway property during their rallies held here in November and December. 




